0x0.name: NotRentExempt
0x0.message: The account's lamport balance is below the rent-exempt minimum. Add more SOL to this account so it meets the rent-exempt threshold.

0x1.name: InsufficientFunds
0x1.message: The token account does not have enough tokens to complete this operation. Check your token balance and try again.

0x2.name: InvalidMint
0x2.message: The mint address provided is not valid. Ensure you are using the correct token mint for this operation.

0x3.name: MintMismatch
0x3.message: The token account is not associated with the specified mint. The source and destination accounts must hold the same token type.

0x4.name: OwnerMismatch
0x4.message: The signing authority does not match the account's owner. Only the account owner can authorize this transaction.

0x5.name: FixedSupply
0x5.message: This token's supply is fixed and new tokens cannot be minted. The mint authority has been disabled.

0x6.name: AlreadyInUse
0x6.message: This account has already been initialized and cannot be initialized again.

0x7.name: InvalidNumberOfProvidedSigners
0x7.message: The number of signers provided does not match what the instruction requires.

0x8.name: InvalidNumberOfRequiredSigners
0x8.message: The number of required signers specified in the account is invalid.

0x9.name: UninitializedState
0x9.message: The token account has not been initialized. Create and initialize the account before using it.

0xa.name: NativeNotSupported
0xa.message: This instruction does not support native SOL token accounts (wrapped SOL).

0xb.name: NonNativeHasBalance
0xb.message: A non-native token account can only be closed if its token balance is zero. Transfer or burn all tokens first.

0xc.name: InvalidInstruction
0xc.message: The instruction data is malformed or contains an unrecognized instruction type.

0xd.name: InvalidState
0xd.message: The account is in an invalid state for the requested operation (e.g., attempting to thaw an account that is not frozen).

0xe.name: Overflow
0xe.message: An arithmetic overflow occurred during the operation. The resulting token amount exceeds the maximum allowed value.

0xf.name: AuthorityTypeNotSupported
0xf.message: The authority type specified is not supported for this account. Check that you are using the correct authority (e.g., MintTokens, FreezeAccount).

0x10.name: MintCannotFreeze
0x10.message: This token mint has no freeze authority set, so its accounts cannot be frozen or thawed.

0x11.name: AccountFrozen
0x11.message: This token account is frozen. All transfers and operations are suspended until the freeze authority thaws the account.

0x12.name: MintDecimalsMismatch
0x12.message: The decimal precision specified in the instruction does not match the mint's actual decimal setting.

0x13.name: NonNativeNotSupported
0x13.message: This instruction only supports native SOL (wrapped SOL) token accounts, not regular SPL token accounts.

0x0.name: InstructionUnpackError
0x0.message: Failed to deserialize the instruction data. The transaction may have been built with an incompatible version of the Metaplex SDK.

0x1.name: InstructionPackError
0x1.message: Failed to serialize the instruction data when building the transaction.

0x2.name: NotRentExempt
0x2.message: The metadata account's lamport balance is below the rent-exempt minimum. Fund the account with enough SOL before proceeding.

0x3.name: AlreadyInitialized
0x3.message: This metadata account has already been created and initialized for the given mint. You cannot create it a second time.

0x4.name: Uninitialized
0x4.message: The metadata account has not been initialized yet. Create the metadata account before trying to update or use it.

0x5.name: InvalidMetadataKey
0x5.message: The provided metadata account address is incorrect. The metadata PDA must be derived from the correct mint address.

0x6.name: InvalidUpdateAuthorityKey
0x6.message: The update authority address does not match the one stored in the metadata account.

0x7.name: UpdateAuthorityIsNotSigner
0x7.message: The update authority must sign this transaction but did not. Ensure the update authority wallet has signed the transaction.

0x8.name: UseAuthorityRecordAlreadyExists
0x8.message: A use authority record already exists for this account. You cannot create a duplicate use authority.

0x9.name: UseAuthorityRecordAlreadyRevoked
0x9.message: The use authority record has already been revoked and can no longer be used to approve operations.

0xa.name: Tombstone
0xa.message: This use authority has been tombstoned (permanently disabled) and cannot be used or reinstated.

0x1f.name: InvalidMasterEdition
0x1f.message: The master edition account provided is invalid or does not match the expected PDA for this mint.

0x20.name: MasterEditionAddMintDecimalsMismatch
0x20.message: A master edition NFT must use a mint with 0 decimal places and a supply of 1.

0x3e.name: NotEnoughTokens
0x3e.message: The wallet does not hold enough tokens to perform this operation. For NFTs, a balance of exactly 1 token is required.

0x46.name: CreatorNotFound
0x46.message: The specified creator address was not found in the metadata's creator array. Verify the creator list on the NFT.
